  "body": "User @baysa from discord reported issues trying to connect the validator with the beacon chain on a dockerized environment.\r\n\r\nReview and fix the issues + add a one liner to spin-up a working setup with both components. Current setup only includes a beacon node.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nDiscord message https://discord.com/channels/593655374469660673/593655641445367808/798215178625351740\r\n\r\nI want to run lodestar using docker compose. Beacon node (beacon-container) configurations:\r\n\r\nbeacon \r\n--testnet pyrmont \r\n--eth1.providerUrl http://geth:8545 \r\n--rootDir /opt/app/beacon \r\n--api.rest.host 0.0.0.0 \r\n--metrics.enabled true \r\n--metrics.serverPort 8008 \r\n--api.rest.enabled true\r\n--api.rest.port 9596\r\n\r\nValidator (validator-container) configurations:\r\n\r\nvalidator \r\n--testnet pyrmont \r\n--server http://beacon:9596 \r\n--keystoresDir /opt/app/keystores \r\n--secretsDir /opt/app/secrets \r\n--validatorsDbDir /opt/app/validator-db\r\n\r\nbut it doesn't work for me, got error (validator-logs shown below). Anyone know how to fix this? thank you\r\n\r\n![unknown](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/104335857-15d58400-54f4-11eb-949e-108a847b3e59.png)\r\n",
